19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6401 of Title 74, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 As used in this act:
23 1. "Extremely low income household" means income not in excess
24 of thirty percent (30%) of the area median income, adjusted for the
Req. No. 10823 Page 1

1 size of the household, as determined by the United States Department
2 of Housing and Urban Development (HUD);
3 2. "Very low income household" means a household income of more
4 than thirty percent (30%) of the area median income but no more than
5 fifty percent (50%) of the area median income, adjusted for the size
6 of the household, as determined by the United States Department of
7 Housing and Urban Development;
8 3. "Low income household" means a household income of more than
9 fifty percent (50%) of the area median income but no more than
10 eighty percent (80%) of the area median income, adjusted for the
11 size of the household, as determined by the United States Department
12 of Housing and Urban Development;
13 4. "Moderate income household" means a household income of more
14 than eighty percent (80%) of the area median income but no more than
15 one hundred twenty percent (120%) of the area median income,
16 adjusted for the size of the household, as determined by the United
17 States Department of Housing and Urban Development; and
18 5. "Middle income household" means a household that has an
19 income of more than one hundred twenty percent (120%) of the area
20 median income but no more than one hundred sixty percent (160%) of
21 the area median income, adjusted for the size of the household, as
22 determined by the United States Department of Housing and Urban
23 Development.
