1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6402 of Title 74, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma Affordable Housing
5 Commission. The Commission shall be composed of sixteen (16)
6 members. The members shall serve as follows:
7 1. Eight members shall be appointed by the President Pro
8 Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate:
9 a. one shall be a Senator from the majority party who
10 shall serve as co-chair of the Commission,
11 b. one shall be a Senator from the minority party who
12 shall serve as co-vice chair of the Commission,
13 c. one shall be a representative of an American Indian
14 Tribe who provides affordable housing in rural areas,
15 whose first term shall be for one (1) year, and then
16 renewable for three-year terms thereafter,
17 d. one shall be a representative from a low income and
18 moderate to low income population-serving financial
19 institution (A Community Development Financial
20 Institution as defined by the Federal Reserve) whose
21 first term shall be for two (2) years, and then
22 renewable for three-year terms thereafter,
23 e. one shall be a representative from a Community Housing
24 Development Organization (CHDO), as determined by the
Req. No. 10823 Page 3

1 United States Department of Housing and Urban
2 Development, whose first term shall be for two (2)
3 years, and then renewable for three-year terms
4 thereafter,
5 f. a representative of building service or construction
6 trades whose first term shall be for two years, and
7 then renewable for three-year terms thereafter,
8 g. one shall be from the Oklahoma Department of Commerce
9 Community Development Division, or his or her
10 designee, whose first term shall be for three (3)
11 years, and then renewable for three one-year terms
12 thereafter, and
13 h. one shall be an Oklahoma representative of the United
14 States Department of Agriculture (USDA);
15 2. Eight members shall be appointed by the Speaker of the
16 Oklahoma House of Representatives:
17 a. one shall be a House member from the majority party
18 who shall serve as co-chair of the Commission,
19 b. one shall be a House member from the minority party
20 who shall serve as co-vice chair of the Commission,
21 c. one shall be a representative from a not-for-profit
22 organization who serves low-income Oklahomans
23 experiencing difficulty in obtaining affordable
