1 B. The Commission shall utilize the Oklahoma Affordable Housing
2 Commission Revolving Fund as authorized in Section 3 of this act.
3 C. The Commission shall utilize the resources available to it
4 in order to address the needs of extremely low income households,
5 very low income households, low income households, moderate income
6 households, and middle income households in order to promote a
7 condition in which suitable housing is available to as many persons
8 as possible.
9 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
10 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6404 of Title 74, unless there
11 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
12 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
13 fund to be designated as the "Oklahoma Affordable Housing Commission
14 Revolving Fund", which shall consist of all monies appropriated,
15 transferred, or otherwise designated to the fund by law. The
16 revolving fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
17 year limitations, and shall be under the administration of the
18 Oklahoma Affordable Housing Commission and shall be budgeted and
19 expended in accordance with the provisions of subsection B of this
20 section for the purpose of improving the stock and affordability of
21 Oklahoma housing.
22 B. No funds shall be budgeted or expended from the Oklahoma
23 Affordable Housing Commission Revolving Fund prior to July 1, 2025,
24 or prior to the approval by the Legislature of promulgated permanent
Req. No. 10823 Page 6

1 rule s by the Commission pursuant to the provisions of the
2 Administrative Procedures Act.
3 C. The Oklahoma Affordable Housing Commission shall promulgate,
4 pursuant to the provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act,
5 permanent rules subject to approval by the Legislature, to
6 implement:
7 1. An initial comprehensive Oklahoma Affordable Housing
8 environmental scan and needs assessment;
9 2. A comprehensive Oklahoma Affordable Housing annual report
10 and action plan;
11 3. Details of the Commission's general duties;
12 4. Reporting requirements of the Commission to the Legislature;
13 5. Evaluate and make recommendations to the Legislature on
14 abatement and exemption incentives to support the development of
15 more affordable housing; and
16 6. Any other rules necessary to carry out the purpose and
17 mission of the Commission as expressed in this act.
18 D. All unencumbered funds remaining in the Oklahoma Affordable
19 Housing Commission Revolving Fund upon the expiration of the
20 Oklahoma Affordable Housing Commission shall be transferred to the
21 State Treasurer for deposit in the General Revenue Fund.
22 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
